                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/171a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Canada</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Complaint is made by Huasteca Petroleum Company and Mexican Petroleum Company
                    that, after they have overpaid taxes levied upon oil, Carranza has given orders
                    forbidding shipments of petroleum. He also forbids further operating until a new
                    decree is issued. This will do great injury to the company mentioned and other
                    oil companies. Will you bring the matter to the attention of Carranza and secure
                    what relief you can?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
